# Overview

This document demonstrates the complete analysis pipeline for the proposed study: **"Attentional Control and the Dual Mechanisms of Retro-Cue Memory Optimization."** All analyses use simulated data to validate the pipeline before data collection.

The pipeline has three stages:

1. CFA: Extract latent attentional control factor scores
2. Mixture Modeling: Decompose continuous recall errors into κ, p~swap~, p~guess~
3. Hypothesis Testing: Link AC factors to mixture model parameters

---

# Step 1: Confirmatory Factor Analysis

## 1.1 Simulate AC Battery Data

We generate data for 6 indicators loading on two correlated latent factors.

```{r cfa-simulate}
N <- 200

# True population parameters
lambda <- c(stroop = 0.65, flanker = 0.70, antisacc = 0.60,
            vsearch = 0.68, capture = 0.62, changeK = 0.72)
phi_12 <- 0.35

# Generate latent scores
Phi <- matrix(c(1, phi_12, phi_12, 1), nrow = 2)
eta <- MASS::mvrnorm(N, mu = c(0, 0), Sigma = Phi)

# Generate observed indicators
error_var <- 1 - lambda^2
ac_data <- data.frame(
  stroop_interf   = lambda[1] * eta[,1] + rnorm(N, 0, sqrt(error_var[1])),
  flanker_interf  = lambda[2] * eta[,1] + rnorm(N, 0, sqrt(error_var[2])),
  antisacc_acc    = lambda[3] * eta[,1] + rnorm(N, 0, sqrt(error_var[3])),
  vsearch_slope   = lambda[4] * eta[,2] + rnorm(N, 0, sqrt(error_var[4])),
  attcapture_cost = lambda[5] * eta[,2] + rnorm(N, 0, sqrt(error_var[5])),
  changedet_K     = lambda[6] * eta[,2] + rnorm(N, 0, sqrt(error_var[6]))
)
```

## 1.2 Fit CFA Model

```{r cfa-fit}
cfa_model <- '
  InhibControl   =~ stroop_interf + flanker_interf + antisacc_acc
  ProcEfficiency =~ vsearch_slope + attcapture_cost + changedet_K
  InhibControl ~~ ProcEfficiency
'

fit <- cfa(cfa_model, data = ac_data, estimator = "MLR", std.lv = TRUE)
```

## 1.3 Evaluate Fit

```{r cfa-fit-indices}
fi <- fitMeasures(fit, c("cfi", "rmsea", "srmr", "chisq", "df", "pvalue"))

tibble(
  Index = c("CFI", "RMSEA", "SRMR"),
  Value = round(fi[c("cfi", "rmsea", "srmr")], 3),
  Target = c("> .95", "< .06", "< .08"),
  Pass = c(fi["cfi"] > .95, fi["rmsea"] < .06, fi["srmr"] < .08)
) %>%
  kable(caption = "CFA Fit Indices") %>%
  kable_styling(bootstrap_options = c("striped", "hover"), full_width = FALSE)
```

## 1.4 Standardized Loadings

```{r cfa-loadings, fig.height=4}
std_load <- parameterEstimates(fit, standardized = TRUE) %>%
  filter(op == "=~") %>%
  mutate(Factor = ifelse(lhs == "InhibControl", 
                         "Inhibitory Control", "Processing Efficiency"))

ggplot(std_load, aes(x = reorder(rhs, std.all), y = std.all, fill = Factor)) +
  geom_col(width = 0.6) +
  geom_hline(yintercept = 0.5, linetype = "dashed", color = "gray40") +
  coord_flip() +
  scale_fill_manual(values = c("#3498DB", "#E67E22")) +
  labs(title = "Standardized Factor Loadings", x = NULL, y = "Loading") +
  theme_minimal(base_size = 13) +
  theme(plot.title = element_text(face = "bold"), legend.position = "bottom")
```

## 1.5 Extract Factor Scores

```{r cfa-scores}
ac_scores <- as.data.frame(lavPredict(fit, type = "lv"))
colnames(ac_scores) <- c("inhibition_z", "efficiency_z")
ac_scores$subject <- 1:N
```

